This paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation in computer vision, specifically for semantic segmentation and object detection tasks. The paper proposes a modification to an existing photorealistic style transfer algorithm to achieve state-of-the-art results in synthetic-to-real domain adaptation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves image processing and graphics, which suggests the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics).
